<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-04T11:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-04T11:29:00-05:00" n="626" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2648</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Archangel</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-04T21:00:00+04:31"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            4, 1918, 9 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 7, 7.36
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>381. <persName corresp="#p_LFO1">Lindley</persName> says 3,000 tons
                                flour will arrive from England 10th September and 6,000 tons
                                additional about the 15th. I hoped we would be first to report food
                                shipments.</p>
                            <p>About 4,800 American troops on three transports arrived here to-day,
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SCGE1">Colonel Stewart</persName>
                                commanding.</p>
                            <p>Naval Lieutenant <persName>Riis</persName> also arrived on transport
                                not touching Murman where he had orders to report from Admiral
                                    <persName>Strauss</persName> but no official designated in
                                order. He brought two boiler makers with orders to report to <hi rend="italic">Olympia</hi>. <persName>Riis</persName> speaks
                                Russian and Esthonian. I have designated him acting naval attaché
                                until otherwise instructed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_FDR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>